I respectfully suggest DIRT-* (figure out your own meaning for the
acronym).  The concept is WS-* without SOAP, right?  If a disciplined
process leads to RESTful solutions, good.  But not all problems are
nails for the REST hammer to solve.  Suggesting that the entire WS-*
stack, including the screws, can just be hammered in like nails,
without first inventing a hammer-driven screw (an actual RESTful 2PC
protocol) is disrespectful.

-Eric
